1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:04,879
[Jalil] <i>I spotted Marcus Reyes</i>
<i>snooping around Zylverix.</i>

2
00:00:04,963 --> 00:00:06,172
And I need to find out why he was there.

3
00:00:06,256 --> 00:00:07,924
Don't worry. I'll help you.

4
00:00:08,008 --> 00:00:10,802
[reporter] <i>Around midnight last night,</i>
<i>police officers</i>

5
00:00:10,885 --> 00:00:13,972
<i>PO3 Condecido and PO3 Vinluan</i>
<i>were shot while on patrol.</i>

6
00:00:14,055 --> 00:00:15,724
[Usman] <i>I talked to Buster earlier.</i>

7
00:00:15,807 --> 00:00:18,977
<i>The CCTV footage</i>
<i>from the time of the crime was wiped out.</i>

8
00:00:19,060 --> 00:00:21,563
You're right.
This was no ordinary accident.

9
00:00:21,646 --> 00:00:24,733
[Lara, in English]
<i>What are you up to, Marcus?</i>

10
00:00:24,816 --> 00:00:27,569
[Marcus] <i>If nobody went in or out</i>

11
00:00:27,652 --> 00:00:30,363
<i>before and after I showed up with Usman,</i>

12
00:00:30,447 --> 00:00:31,364
<i>it's possible he was never transferred.</i>

13
00:00:31,448 --> 00:00:33,783
<i>We were just looking in the wrong spot.</i>

14
00:00:33,867 --> 00:00:36,745
[Azuelo, in English] <i>This is</i>
<i>a full-scale search for Datu Rahman.</i>

15
00:00:36,828 --> 00:00:40,248
<i>Lock down the whole perimeter.</i>
<i>If he's in this building,</i>

16
00:00:40,331 --> 00:00:43,001
<i>see to it he never slips from our grasp.</i>

17
00:00:43,084 --> 00:00:44,252
[in English] <i>Understood?</i>

18
00:00:45,211 --> 00:00:46,421
[officer] <i>Sir Marcus.</i>

19
00:00:47,130 --> 00:00:48,631
<i>Nothing in the other wing.</i>

20
00:00:48,715 --> 00:00:50,133
<i>Unit 1 has also cleared the storage area.</i>

21
00:00:51,134 --> 00:00:52,802
[Lara] <i>Negative, sir.</i>
<i>We couldn't find the target.</i>

22
00:00:52,886 --> 00:00:55,555
Sir Marcus, you seem a little rusty.

23
00:00:56,264 --> 00:00:57,724
They didn't find Father.

24
00:00:57,807 --> 00:01:00,935
[suspenseful music playing]

25
00:01:02,395 --> 00:01:06,441
[Azuelo] <i>I committed four officers</i>
<i>to guard a ghost building!</i>

26
00:01:06,524 --> 00:01:10,236
[in English] I'm giving you
until 0200 hours.

27
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:12,363
[Azuelo] <i>If you got nothing</i>
<i>to show by then,</i>

28
00:01:12,447 --> 00:01:15,200
<i>you will abort the operation</i>
<i>and drop that lead!</i>

29
00:01:15,283 --> 00:01:17,285
[Marcus] <i>There's no elevator</i>
<i>in the blueprint.</i>

30
00:01:19,329 --> 00:01:21,706
Transfer Datu Rahman at once!

31
00:01:21,790 --> 00:01:23,625
[Marcus] <i>If it wasn't</i>
<i>in the original blueprint,</i>

32
00:01:23,708 --> 00:01:25,919
<i>they might be hiding something here.</i>

33
00:01:27,253 --> 00:01:29,339
- [lock rattles]
- [Jalil grunts]

34
00:01:29,422 --> 00:01:31,007
[grunting and groaning]

35
00:01:31,090 --> 00:01:33,635
[man shouts]

36
00:01:33,718 --> 00:01:35,345
[Marcus] <i>Take me to Datu Rahman!</i>

37
00:01:35,428 --> 00:01:36,846
‪[music intensifies, concludes]

38
00:01:38,890 --> 00:01:43,061
[mysterious theme music playing]

39
00:01:54,239 --> 00:01:58,034
[suspenseful music playing]

40
00:02:00,578 --> 00:02:01,830
[elevator doors sliding]

41
00:02:01,913 --> 00:02:03,623
[Marcus grunts]

42
00:02:10,004 --> 00:02:11,381
[goon 1 groans]

43
00:02:13,508 --> 00:02:16,886
[coughing, breathing laboriously]

44
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:22,684
[suspenseful music continues]

45
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:32,777
[Marcus shouts]

46
00:02:32,861 --> 00:02:33,736
[gunshots]

47
00:02:35,488 --> 00:02:36,573
[thwacking]

48
00:02:36,656 --> 00:02:38,116
- [grunts]
- [gunshot]

49
00:02:38,199 --> 00:02:39,159
[goon 1 grunts]

50
00:02:41,161 --> 00:02:42,954
[goon 1 grunts, groans]

51
00:02:43,037 --> 00:02:47,667
[suspenseful music continues]

52
00:02:55,758 --> 00:02:56,968
[loud thud]

53
00:02:57,051 --> 00:03:01,222
- [gunshots]
- [man grunts]

54
00:03:01,306 --> 00:03:02,348
[goon 2 exclaims]

55
00:03:02,432 --> 00:03:03,850
- [gunshot]
- [grunts]

56
00:03:03,933 --> 00:03:07,270
[rapid gunfire]

57
00:03:07,353 --> 00:03:11,691
[suspenseful music continues]

58
00:03:18,823 --> 00:03:20,241
[gun clicks]

59
00:03:22,660 --> 00:03:24,954
[grunting and groaning]

60
00:03:25,038 --> 00:03:25,997
[gunshot]

61
00:03:29,083 --> 00:03:30,585
[groaning]

62
00:03:30,668 --> 00:03:31,628
Who are you?!

63
00:03:32,545 --> 00:03:33,713
[Marcus grunts]

64
00:03:34,756 --> 00:03:37,425
Come with me. You need to come with me.

65
00:03:37,508 --> 00:03:39,177
I'm not coming with you!

66
00:03:42,847 --> 00:03:45,725
[suspenseful music continues]

67
00:04:01,366 --> 00:04:05,578
[suspenseful music continues]

68
00:04:05,662 --> 00:04:07,497
[elevator bell dings]

69
00:04:08,665 --> 00:04:10,583
[Datu huffs, whinces]

70
00:04:13,044 --> 00:04:15,004
- [tires screeching]
- [engine revving]

71
00:04:15,088 --> 00:04:16,673
[gate clanging]

72
00:04:18,633 --> 00:04:20,802
[brakes squealing]

73
00:04:20,885 --> 00:04:24,514
[suspenseful music continues]

74
00:04:27,141 --> 00:04:31,688
[rapid gunfire]

75
00:04:33,856 --> 00:04:34,816
[distant rapid gunfire]

76
00:04:34,899 --> 00:04:38,111
[gunshots]

77
00:04:42,031 --> 00:04:42,991
[officer] Come on!

78
00:04:43,074 --> 00:04:44,701
[suspenseful music continues]

79
00:04:44,784 --> 00:04:48,079
[gunshots]

80
00:04:49,747 --> 00:04:50,581
[officer shouts]

81
00:04:50,665 --> 00:04:52,709
- [rapid gunfire]
- [inaudible]

82
00:04:52,792 --> 00:04:57,213
[gunshots]

83
00:04:59,299 --> 00:05:00,216
They're after you!

84
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:02,677
[man exclaims] Oh.

85
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:03,761
Let's go!

86
00:05:03,845 --> 00:05:06,681
[rapid gunfire]

87
00:05:07,765 --> 00:05:09,225
Come on!

88
00:05:12,562 --> 00:05:13,604
[gunshots]

89
00:05:17,025 --> 00:05:20,903
[suspenseful music continues]

90
00:05:20,987 --> 00:05:26,492
[grunting and groaning]

91
00:05:27,285 --> 00:05:31,289
[gunshots]

92
00:05:32,457 --> 00:05:34,959
- [body thuds]
- [goon 3 screams]

93
00:05:35,043 --> 00:05:36,878
- [man shouts]
- [gunshot]

94
00:05:36,961 --> 00:05:41,049
[gunshots]

95
00:05:42,091 --> 00:05:43,926
[suspenseful music continues]

96
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:45,053
[gun clicks]

97
00:05:46,387 --> 00:05:47,263
[guns clatter]

98
00:05:51,392 --> 00:05:55,521
[music intensifying]

99
00:05:59,817 --> 00:06:01,569
[grunting and groaning]

100
00:06:01,652 --> 00:06:04,906
- [gunshots]
- [grunts]

101
00:06:04,989 --> 00:06:06,157
- [thwack]
- [groans]

102
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:07,992
- [rapid gunfire]
- [tires screeching]

103
00:06:12,789 --> 00:06:15,500
- [tires screech]
- [brakes squealing]

104
00:06:16,250 --> 00:06:17,085
[goon 5 shouts]

105
00:06:20,213 --> 00:06:23,633
[suspenseful music continues]

106
00:06:28,930 --> 00:06:30,014
[muffled grunting]

107
00:06:30,098 --> 00:06:34,227
[overlapping shouting]

108
00:06:34,310 --> 00:06:36,187
[man 1] Hey!

109
00:06:38,689 --> 00:06:40,274
[man 1] Hey!

110
00:06:42,276 --> 00:06:43,319
[man 2] Come on! Hurry!

111
00:06:43,402 --> 00:06:47,865
[tires screeching]

112
00:06:50,034 --> 00:06:54,080
[suspenseful music continues]

113
00:06:57,625 --> 00:07:01,504
[phone ringing]

114
00:07:04,757 --> 00:07:08,678
- [softly] Brother, what's your status?
- My suspicion was right.

115
00:07:09,220 --> 00:07:10,596
I have Datu Rahman.

116
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:15,393
[in Arabic] Praise be to God.

117
00:07:18,646 --> 00:07:19,564
What's your plan?

118
00:07:20,148 --> 00:07:21,566
I need your help.

119
00:07:21,649 --> 00:07:25,820
[sinister music playing]

120
00:07:32,660 --> 00:07:35,746
- [camera shutters clicking]
- [overlapping chatter]

121
00:07:35,830 --> 00:07:38,082
[overlapping dialogue]

122
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:41,085
[officer 1] Everyone!
Stay back! Stay back!

123
00:07:41,169 --> 00:07:43,254
[officer 2] You can cover
your news reports later!

124
00:07:43,337 --> 00:07:45,882
[reporter 1] Just one interview, sir!

125
00:07:45,965 --> 00:07:48,843
[officer 1] I told you to step back!

126
00:07:48,926 --> 00:07:50,803
- [reporter 3] Sir!
- [officer 3] Step back!

127
00:07:50,887 --> 00:07:51,888
[reporter 4] Sir, just one interview!

128
00:07:52,889 --> 00:07:54,557
[officer 4] Step back!

129
00:07:55,725 --> 00:07:59,854
[ominous music playing]

130
00:08:12,408 --> 00:08:15,995
[music intensifies]

131
00:08:36,849 --> 00:08:38,518
[metal cage rattling]

132
00:08:38,601 --> 00:08:40,102
[Jalil grunts, coughs]

133
00:08:41,646 --> 00:08:42,855
[man] Stand up!

134
00:08:42,939 --> 00:08:44,065
- Go ahead and pick him up!
- [Jalil grunts]

135
00:08:44,148 --> 00:08:46,108
- Start walking!
- [Jalil grunts]

136
00:08:49,237 --> 00:08:51,697
[Jalil grunting]

137
00:08:51,781 --> 00:08:53,991
- [man] Stand up!
- [Jalil groans]

138
00:08:55,618 --> 00:08:56,619
[man] Stop fighting back!

139
00:08:57,245 --> 00:09:01,707
[grunting, groaning]

140
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:04,544
[grunting, groaning]

141
00:09:05,419 --> 00:09:06,587
[Jalil grunts]

142
00:09:07,797 --> 00:09:09,090
You just don't give up, do you?

143
00:09:09,173 --> 00:09:11,467
[grunts, groans]

144
00:09:12,134 --> 00:09:13,344
[man grunts]

145
00:09:13,427 --> 00:09:14,554
[man] Carry him!

146
00:09:17,598 --> 00:09:21,143
- [tense music playing]
- [camera shutters clicking]

147
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,608
[Lara] Where have you been?

148
00:09:33,531 --> 00:09:35,283
- [grunts]
- [gunshots]

149
00:09:35,366 --> 00:09:37,201
- [grunts]
- [gunshots]

150
00:09:37,285 --> 00:09:39,453
You must come with me.

151
00:09:40,496 --> 00:09:41,622
You need to come with me right now.

152
00:09:41,706 --> 00:09:43,749
[gunshots]

153
00:09:45,543 --> 00:09:47,169
I was on my way home
when I received the alert.

154
00:09:50,798 --> 00:09:52,216
- What happened here?
- [suspenseful music]

155
00:09:57,305 --> 00:09:59,724
[camera shutters clicking]

156
00:09:59,807 --> 00:10:03,394
[overlapping chatter]

157
00:10:06,230 --> 00:10:08,482
[Azuelo] Goddamn it! Reyes! Angeles!

158
00:10:08,566 --> 00:10:10,067
What happened here?!

159
00:10:10,151 --> 00:10:14,238
[music intensifies]

160
00:10:16,657 --> 00:10:17,867
‪[music ends]

161
00:10:17,950 --> 00:10:19,327
- [Jalil coughs]
- [suspenseful music playing]

162
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:20,244
Who the hell are you?

163
00:10:21,245 --> 00:10:23,831
Why did you kill our comrades?

164
00:10:24,832 --> 00:10:26,292
Are you planning to help
Datu Rahman escape?

165
00:10:26,375 --> 00:10:27,293
[gasps]

166
00:10:27,376 --> 00:10:30,921
[suspenseful music playing]

167
00:10:32,131 --> 00:10:33,883
Where is Father?!

168
00:10:35,051 --> 00:10:36,344
[shouting, grunting]

169
00:10:37,887 --> 00:10:39,138
Why can't you answer the question?

170
00:10:39,221 --> 00:10:41,223
[grunting, groaning]

171
00:10:41,307 --> 00:10:44,769
[Jalil gasps]

172
00:10:44,852 --> 00:10:46,437
[man] Enough! [grunts]

173
00:10:52,276 --> 00:10:56,113
[tense music playing]

174
00:11:02,703 --> 00:11:05,247
[in English] Reyes. Check that area.

175
00:11:06,916 --> 00:11:08,459
Angeles, you check that area.

176
00:11:08,542 --> 00:11:09,543
[in English] Yes, sir.

177
00:11:10,503 --> 00:11:14,340
[tense music continues]

178
00:11:19,678 --> 00:11:20,679
[crunches]

179
00:11:20,763 --> 00:11:22,056
‪[sinister music playing]

180
00:11:36,946 --> 00:11:38,322
[Azuelo] There's a key.

181
00:11:39,615 --> 00:11:41,075
What could it be for?

182
00:11:41,575 --> 00:11:45,746
[tense music playing]

183
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:57,299
- [Datu Rahman groans]
- [Marcus] Hurry!

184
00:11:58,217 --> 00:12:01,262
[grunts]

185
00:12:02,638 --> 00:12:04,390
[Datu Rahman groans]

186
00:12:04,473 --> 00:12:06,183
[elevator dings]

187
00:12:06,267 --> 00:12:09,270
- [grunting, groaning]
- [elevator dings]

188
00:12:12,982 --> 00:12:13,941
[key thuds]

189
00:12:14,692 --> 00:12:16,402
[grunting, groaning]

190
00:12:19,572 --> 00:12:21,657
This is a high-security bypass key, sir.

191
00:12:21,740 --> 00:12:25,202
[suspenseful music playing]

192
00:12:25,286 --> 00:12:28,956
Team, look for a concealed key way.

193
00:12:29,039 --> 00:12:32,460
Or any suspicious-looking access points.

194
00:12:32,543 --> 00:12:34,545
- [in English] Move.
- [officers, in English] Yes, sir!

195
00:12:36,672 --> 00:12:38,799
Isn't that for the elevator, sir?

196
00:12:39,675 --> 00:12:41,802
This is the last place
we haven't opened in the building.

197
00:12:41,886 --> 00:12:45,306
[tense music continues]

198
00:13:02,698 --> 00:13:06,410
[tense music continues]

199
00:13:11,540 --> 00:13:12,917
- [key rattling]
- [elevator dings]

200
00:13:16,253 --> 00:13:18,130
[in English] Goddammit.

201
00:13:24,887 --> 00:13:25,804
[in English] Let's go!

202
00:13:40,444 --> 00:13:42,404
[elevator dings]

203
00:13:43,197 --> 00:13:44,657
[elevator dings]

204
00:13:45,199 --> 00:13:49,703
[tense music continues]

205
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:04,176
Stay alert!

206
00:14:04,718 --> 00:14:06,387
[in English] Check and secure the area.

207
00:14:07,096 --> 00:14:08,097
[in English] Move!

208
00:14:17,231 --> 00:14:19,775
[suspenseful sting]

209
00:14:31,328 --> 00:14:32,538
[in English] Check the area!

210
00:14:32,621 --> 00:14:36,584
[tense music continues]

211
00:14:43,132 --> 00:14:44,258
[in English] Clear!

212
00:15:05,613 --> 00:15:09,825
[tense music continues]

213
00:15:20,753 --> 00:15:25,174
[tense music continues]

214
00:15:25,257 --> 00:15:26,467
My hunch was right.

215
00:15:26,967 --> 00:15:29,011
Datu Rahman was brought here.

216
00:15:29,094 --> 00:15:31,305
Looks like he was just recently
moved out of here.

217
00:15:32,514 --> 00:15:34,767
So, who took him,

218
00:15:36,644 --> 00:15:38,312
and where did they take him?!

219
00:15:45,945 --> 00:15:49,657
[tense music intensifying]

220
00:15:55,621 --> 00:15:57,915
[Azuelo] How did this happen, Agent Reyes?

221
00:15:57,998 --> 00:16:00,542
You said you were going
to find Datu Rahman.

222
00:16:01,168 --> 00:16:04,380
But how come he's missing again?!

223
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:06,340
Sir, I am doing my best.

224
00:16:07,424 --> 00:16:10,678
- For now, I'm tracking--
- [in English] That's not enough!

225
00:16:12,388 --> 00:16:15,057
With how long we've been
looking for Datu Rahman,

226
00:16:15,140 --> 00:16:17,601
this is getting ridiculous!

227
00:16:17,685 --> 00:16:21,230
You don't even know if he was kidnapped
or ran away on his own.

228
00:16:21,313 --> 00:16:22,898
All the guards were dead,

229
00:16:22,982 --> 00:16:24,817
including those who were watching him.

230
00:16:26,443 --> 00:16:28,946
It is possible that his accomplices

231
00:16:29,029 --> 00:16:30,656
have something to do with this.

232
00:16:30,739 --> 00:16:32,241
Sir, it's also possible

233
00:16:32,324 --> 00:16:34,618
that there's a third party
involved who took him.

234
00:16:35,911 --> 00:16:37,538
There are a lot
of possible explanations, sir!

235
00:16:37,621 --> 00:16:39,581
I don't care!

236
00:16:41,083 --> 00:16:43,419
[Azuelo] After doing so much searching,

237
00:16:44,003 --> 00:16:45,504
it's my name that's dragged
through the mud!

238
00:16:48,382 --> 00:16:52,428
Whether he escaped on his own
or was kidnapped by someone,

239
00:16:52,928 --> 00:16:58,058
what matters is that we find Datu Rahman!

240
00:16:59,309 --> 00:17:00,519
Did I make myself clear?!

241
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:02,229
[in English] Yes, sir.

242
00:17:02,813 --> 00:17:03,647
[man] Get them.

243
00:17:03,731 --> 00:17:07,109
[reporters clamoring]

244
00:17:09,528 --> 00:17:12,239
[reporter 1] Please, sir,
we need a statement!

245
00:17:12,781 --> 00:17:15,409
[reporter 2] Director Azuelo,
how many confirmed casualties are there?

246
00:17:15,492 --> 00:17:17,453
Is this a raid or a feud
between crime syndicates?

247
00:17:17,536 --> 00:17:19,288
[reporter 3] Is Datu Rahman
found inside the building?

248
00:17:19,371 --> 00:17:21,081
Is he the target of this operation,

249
00:17:21,165 --> 00:17:22,791
or is he the mastermind behind the ambush?

250
00:17:23,876 --> 00:17:27,629
Agent Reyes is the OIC of TFA.

251
00:17:27,713 --> 00:17:31,592
He is the lead investigator in this case.

252
00:17:32,134 --> 00:17:33,761
He should be the one you're talking to.

253
00:17:34,678 --> 00:17:38,015
[reporters clamoring] Sir! Sir! Sir!

254
00:17:38,599 --> 00:17:39,808
[Marcus] As of now,

255
00:17:39,892 --> 00:17:41,727
our investigation is not yet over.

256
00:17:41,810 --> 00:17:44,938
<i>We are yet not able to release</i>
<i>an official statement.</i>

257
00:17:45,022 --> 00:17:47,608
You conducted a lockdown
in this building last night.

258
00:17:47,691 --> 00:17:49,109
Why did it lead to a shootout?

259
00:17:49,193 --> 00:17:52,029
[in English] Is this a miscount
on intelligence?

260
00:17:52,112 --> 00:17:54,239
Did Datu Rahman escape once again?

261
00:17:54,907 --> 00:17:56,325
There's no confirmation yet.

262
00:17:56,408 --> 00:18:01,580
For now, let's not jump
to baseless conclusions.

263
00:18:02,539 --> 00:18:04,249
We will still follow
the appropriate measures

264
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:05,626
for this crime scene.

265
00:18:06,835 --> 00:18:07,920
<i>Thank you.</i>

266
00:18:08,003 --> 00:18:09,505
- Mr. Omar.
- Hmm?

267
00:18:10,130 --> 00:18:12,466
Jalil was at that exact building
last night.

268
00:18:13,634 --> 00:18:16,136
I was helping him scout the area
before the police arrived.

269
00:18:16,220 --> 00:18:18,597
What?! What was he doing there?

270
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:21,016
He suspected that Datu Rahman
was kept there.

271
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:24,686
[groans in distress] Oh my God! Jalil!

272
00:18:24,770 --> 00:18:27,898
- Rashid!
- I'll give him a call.

273
00:18:27,981 --> 00:18:30,442
[Norhana] Omar… Jalil!

274
00:18:30,526 --> 00:18:32,903
[suspenseful music playing]

275
00:18:32,986 --> 00:18:34,488
[phone beeping disconnect]

276
00:18:34,571 --> 00:18:36,156
- [Jamilah] Peace be upon you!
- Hey!

277
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:37,741
I left my--

278
00:18:39,409 --> 00:18:40,619
Jamilah!

279
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:43,247
Why the long faces?

280
00:18:45,874 --> 00:18:47,584
Did something happen to Jalil?

281
00:18:47,668 --> 00:18:50,879
[suspenseful music continues]

282
00:18:56,468 --> 00:18:58,345
[sighs]

283
00:19:07,813 --> 00:19:10,399
[ominous music playing]

284
00:19:15,988 --> 00:19:18,615
[grunting, groaning]

285
00:19:19,491 --> 00:19:21,785
- [Jalil groans in pain]
- [Marcus grunts]

286
00:19:25,122 --> 00:19:26,707
[both grunting]

287
00:19:27,499 --> 00:19:30,878
[both grunting]

288
00:19:31,753 --> 00:19:33,505
Just who are you?

289
00:19:36,091 --> 00:19:38,051
Are you the man I saw earlier?

290
00:19:38,802 --> 00:19:41,096
You also plan to save Datu Rahman.

291
00:19:46,185 --> 00:19:49,062
[ominous music continues]

292
00:19:52,524 --> 00:19:54,401
- Boss.
- [Jalil grunts]

293
00:19:54,484 --> 00:19:56,320
Looks like this is the man
you're looking for.

294
00:19:56,403 --> 00:19:57,654
[Jalil groaning in pain]

295
00:19:57,738 --> 00:19:58,947
The one with the huge reward on his head.

296
00:19:59,990 --> 00:20:00,991
[Jalil gags]

297
00:20:02,784 --> 00:20:03,785
[Jalil grunts]

298
00:20:03,869 --> 00:20:06,955
And he's also the one
who killed our men in Zylverix.

299
00:20:07,706 --> 00:20:09,124
And I found out something.

300
00:20:10,167 --> 00:20:11,835
He's Datu Rahman's son.

301
00:20:12,711 --> 00:20:14,671
[Felix] Alright, I'm on my way.

302
00:20:14,755 --> 00:20:17,966
[ominous music playing]

303
00:20:18,884 --> 00:20:21,511
- [knife slashes]
- [both grunting]

304
00:20:21,595 --> 00:20:23,847
[chuckling]

305
00:20:31,021 --> 00:20:32,189
[Lara] <i>What happened?</i>

306
00:20:32,272 --> 00:20:33,106
‪[panicked breathing]

307
00:20:33,857 --> 00:20:35,984
<i>How did they find Datu Rahman?</i>

308
00:20:36,068 --> 00:20:37,569
[Lara gasps]

309
00:20:37,653 --> 00:20:39,446
<i>Did they find the CCTV footage?</i>

310
00:20:40,739 --> 00:20:43,283
<i>Who removed the CCTV footage?</i>

311
00:20:44,785 --> 00:20:46,119
[screaming]

312
00:20:46,203 --> 00:20:49,748
[unsettling music playing]

313
00:20:49,831 --> 00:20:52,918
[breathing heavily]

314
00:20:53,502 --> 00:20:56,421
How did this happen? How did this happen?!

315
00:20:57,256 --> 00:20:59,925
Who took you?! Who?!

316
00:21:00,008 --> 00:21:01,635
[breathing heavily]

317
00:21:03,512 --> 00:21:07,307
- [breathing heavily]
- [unsettling music continues]

318
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:09,851
[Jalil] Where is Father?

319
00:21:11,019 --> 00:21:12,938
Where is Datu Rahman?

320
00:21:13,021 --> 00:21:14,523
You're tough, huh?

321
00:21:19,444 --> 00:21:22,698
- [ominous music playing]
- [metal thuds]

322
00:21:24,783 --> 00:21:28,036
[Jalil grunts]

323
00:21:29,997 --> 00:21:31,373
[Jalil groans]

324
00:21:32,457 --> 00:21:34,751
My boss will deal with you.

325
00:21:35,377 --> 00:21:36,795
[groans]

326
00:21:37,921 --> 00:21:40,048
[in Arabic] There is no god but Allah.

327
00:21:40,924 --> 00:21:41,758
‪[disdainful scoff]

328
00:21:42,801 --> 00:21:45,053
[grunting]

329
00:21:45,137 --> 00:21:45,971
Help me!

330
00:21:46,054 --> 00:21:49,766
[grunting, shouting]

331
00:21:49,850 --> 00:21:53,687
- [canister thuds]
- [gas hissing]

332
00:21:54,604 --> 00:21:57,899
[man grunts]

333
00:21:57,983 --> 00:22:01,945
[rapid gunfire]

334
00:22:05,782 --> 00:22:08,201
[Jalil groaning]

335
00:22:17,586 --> 00:22:21,173
[unsettling music playing]

336
00:22:23,550 --> 00:22:25,260
You're coming with us.

337
00:22:26,136 --> 00:22:28,555
[tense music playing]

338
00:22:32,184 --> 00:22:34,644
[tires screeching]

339
00:22:36,521 --> 00:22:40,567
[intriguing music playing]

340
00:22:59,336 --> 00:23:03,590
[intriguing music continues]

341
00:23:22,984 --> 00:23:26,863
[intriguing music continues]

342
00:23:32,077 --> 00:23:35,205
[chains rattling]

343
00:23:35,288 --> 00:23:39,626
[ominous music playing]

344
00:23:44,131 --> 00:23:45,966
- [screaming]
- [chain rattles]

345
00:23:47,050 --> 00:23:49,678
[laughing maniacally]

346
00:23:49,761 --> 00:23:51,805
[man] Help! Help me!

347
00:23:51,888 --> 00:23:53,890
- [gunshots]
- Idiot!

348
00:23:54,641 --> 00:23:57,018
Morons! Useless!

349
00:23:57,102 --> 00:23:58,395
Bastards!

350
00:24:03,358 --> 00:24:04,776
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you, Yusuf.

351
00:24:05,569 --> 00:24:06,987
[in Arabic] And peace be upon you too.

352
00:24:07,070 --> 00:24:09,072
Have you seen Jalil…

353
00:24:09,823 --> 00:24:11,199
Have you noticed my nephew?

354
00:24:11,283 --> 00:24:14,077
Oh yeah, I saw him leave yesterday.

355
00:24:14,161 --> 00:24:16,413
But I haven't seen him come back yet.

356
00:24:17,539 --> 00:24:19,040
Have you checked the apartment?

357
00:24:19,124 --> 00:24:22,294
Yeah. I've been knocking for a while,
but no one's answering.

358
00:24:22,878 --> 00:24:24,546
[sighs]

359
00:24:24,629 --> 00:24:26,339
[dialing tones beeping]

360
00:24:27,299 --> 00:24:29,259
[phone operator, in English]
<i>The subscriber cannot be reached.</i>

361
00:24:29,342 --> 00:24:30,468
<i>Please try again later.</i>

362
00:24:31,219 --> 00:24:32,971
[in Arabic] Oh, Allah.

363
00:24:33,054 --> 00:24:34,347
Where are you, Jalil?

364
00:24:37,475 --> 00:24:39,477
[thuds]

365
00:24:40,645 --> 00:24:42,856
[Jalil panting] You bastards!

366
00:24:44,399 --> 00:24:47,861
Let me go! Let me go!

367
00:24:48,653 --> 00:24:53,909
[grunting]

368
00:24:55,785 --> 00:24:58,955
- [breathing heavily]
- [door clicks open]

369
00:24:59,789 --> 00:25:03,627
[music intensifying]

370
00:25:15,347 --> 00:25:18,433
Who took you when you were supposed
to be transferred to the facility?

371
00:25:18,516 --> 00:25:22,062
Just answer my questions,
and I'll personally take you home.

372
00:25:22,145 --> 00:25:23,271
Where would I even go home to?

373
00:25:23,355 --> 00:25:25,190
[Rahman] <i>You burned our homes down.</i>

374
00:25:25,273 --> 00:25:28,443
<i>You destroyed our peaceful lives!</i>

375
00:25:28,526 --> 00:25:31,029
But we also lost many on our side.

376
00:25:31,112 --> 00:25:32,280
Just to get you!

377
00:25:32,364 --> 00:25:35,242
[Marcus] <i>Why are you so important?</i>
<i>Who are you really?</i>

378
00:25:35,325 --> 00:25:37,327
<i>I'm sure he's hiding something.</i>

379
00:25:37,410 --> 00:25:39,537
<i>He's the key to all of this chaos.</i>

380
00:25:39,621 --> 00:25:43,416
They won't hesitate to kill you
once they find out what you're doing.

381
00:25:43,500 --> 00:25:46,002
[Marcus] <i>I need to find out the truth</i>
<i>before they kill me.</i>

382
00:25:46,086 --> 00:25:47,796
- Any news on Jalil?
- None yet.

383
00:25:47,879 --> 00:25:50,632
I've talked to everyone I trust.

384
00:25:50,715 --> 00:25:52,342
But no one knows where Jalil is.

385
00:25:52,425 --> 00:25:54,344
But what if something bad
happened to Jalil?

386
00:25:54,427 --> 00:25:55,762
[Omar] <i>Your brother is strong.</i>

387
00:25:55,845 --> 00:25:58,640
<i>Let's trust in Allah</i>
<i>that he's safe wherever he is.</i>

388
00:25:59,224 --> 00:26:01,351
How can you be a general

389
00:26:01,434 --> 00:26:06,106
when you haven't done
anything right from the start?

390
00:26:06,189 --> 00:26:09,734
[Angeles] <i>Did you know</i>
<i>even the Muslim Affairs office</i>

391
00:26:09,818 --> 00:26:13,530
<i>is already watching you closely?</i>

392
00:26:13,613 --> 00:26:19,411
<i>That's why they're sending</i>
<i>someone here to monitor you.</i>

393
00:26:19,494 --> 00:26:25,000
Until now, we still don't know
who's doing this to us!

394
00:26:25,083 --> 00:26:27,752
We need to find Datu Rahman!

395
00:26:27,836 --> 00:26:28,962
[Marcus] <i>I checked the census.</i>

396
00:26:29,045 --> 00:26:31,631
There's no registered Rahman Abubakar.

397
00:26:31,715 --> 00:26:34,384
You're not Datu Rahman. Who are you?
